Package Model

Class Intersection

java.lang.Object
Model.Intersection
Direct Known Subclasses:
Stop
public class Intersection extends Object
Intersection is the class that defines a location on the map. An intersection is composed of:
  • A unique id.
  • A latitude.
  • A longitude.
  • The list of all segments that are originated from this intersection.
  • An indication about if the intersection was visited when computing the shortest path (Dijkstra algorithm), updated at each call of Dijkstra.
Intersections are created when loading a map by parsing an XML map file.
Intersection is the ancestor of Stop class.
Author:
H4122

    • Intersection

      public Intersection()
      Default Class constructor. Id and coordinates are set to zero. The list of segments originated from this intersection is empty. The intersection is not visited.

    • Intersection

      public Intersection​(long id, float latitude, float longitude)

      Parameters:

      latitude - Its latitude on the map.
      longitude - Its longitude on the map.

    • getIntersectionVisited

      public Model.Visited getIntersectionVisited()
      intersectionVisited indicates if an intersection was visited when computing the shortest path (Dijkstra algorithm). This intersection can be:
      • WHITE: the intersection is not visited yet.
      • GREY: the intersection is visited and the shortest path to it is not found yet.
      • BLACK: the intersection was visited and the shortest path to it was found yet.
      Returns:
      The status of this intersection during the Dijkstra algorithm.
      See Also:
      Visited, Map.computeShortestPath(Stop, ArrayList)

    • equals

      public boolean equals​(Object obj)
      Overrides equals method in Object class. Compares the object in parameter to this intersection. The specified object is identical to this intersection if it is an intersection and it has the same id, same coordinates (latitude and longitude) and same list of originated segments as this intersection.
      Overrides:
      equals in class Object
      Parameters:
      obj - The object to be compared with.
      Returns:
      TRUE if the specified object and this intersection are identical, FALSE otherwise.
